    dc:title "Revision of the genus Polymerus (Heteroptera: Miridae) in the Eastern Hemisphere. Part 1: Subgenera Polymerus, Pachycentrum subgen. nov. and new genus Dichelocentrum gen. nov." ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5079633>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5079637>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5079651>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5079584> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5079633>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Parameres of Charagochilus species. Right (A, F, I, L, O) and left (B–E, G, H, J, K, M, N, P, Q) parameres. A- C, Ch. spiralifer; D, E, Ch. flavipes; F–H, Ch. bimaculatus; I–K, Ch. obscuratus; L–N, Ch. consanguineus comb. nov.; O–Q, Ch. aureus comb. nov. Left (B, D, G, J, M, P) and posterior (C, E, H, K, N, Q) view. Scale bare: 0.14 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5079633/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5079637>
    dc:description "FIGURE 21. Vesica of Charagochilus species. A, B, Ch. spiralifer; C, D, Ch. flavipes comb. nov. Left (A, C) and right (B, D) view. ab.bab—anterior branch of baso-apical sclerotized band; arl—anterior right lobe; as—anterior spicule; lsc—left serrate carina; mrl—medial right lobe; ms—medial spicule; pa—posterior apex of vesica; pb.bab—posterior branch of baso-apical sclerotized band; prl—posterior right lobe; ps—posterior spicule. Scale bare: 0.14 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5079637/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5079651>
    dc:description "FIGURE 25. Inner female genitalia of Charagochilus species. A, B, Ch. spiralifer; C, D, Ch. flavipes comb. nov. Gynatrium, dorsal view (A, C), posterior wall of gynatrium(B, D), ventral view. ts—tectal sclerites. Scale bare: 0.14 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5079651/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5079584>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Structure of theca. A, theca of Polymerus nigrita; B, theca of Dichelocentrum longirostre; C, apical blade of theca of Dichelocentrum longirostre; D, apical blade of theca of Charagochilus gyllenhalii. Anterior (A, B) and anterio-inferior view (C, D). Scale bare: 0.14 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5079584/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

